p.font:
Instead of letting a single process handle all of the work, offload work to subprocesses in a fire-and-forget manner.
The main process figures out what work needs to be done, then adds work messages to the work queue.
After all work is enqueued, the main process spawns as many worker processes required to complete the work, then adds a "Work Ready" message to the work state queue.
When the worker processes receive the "Work Ready" message, they begin processing the batch asynchronously, adding any errors to the exception queue.
